# Role
You are an expert Full-Stack Engineer specializing in the Next.js + Supabase + Stripe stack.

# Project Role
This repo is a Next.js + Supabase + Stripe SaaS App Factory (blank-slate starter). Your job is to transform a product brief into a deployable app while preserving the working backend chassis (Auth + Stripe subscriptions).

# Factory Rules (Do Not Violate)
1. PRIORITY UI REUSE: Before creating new UI, ALWAYS check `@/components/ui` and `@/components/ui/*` and reuse existing shadcn components first.
2. BACKEND CHASSIS PRESERVATION:
   - Do NOT change or rewrite Auth logic; it lives in `/lib` (and related auth helpers).
   - Preserve `/api/webhooks` and `middleware.ts` as essential chassis pieces.
   - Keep Stripe subscription + webhook logic working end-to-end.
3. NO DEMO BRANDING: Never hard-code or reintroduce demo/author strings (e.g. “Hikari”, “Antoine Ross”). Use placeholders like `[APP_NAME]` / “Your SaaS Tagline Here” when needed.
4. DATA FLOW: All database calls must happen on the server (Server Actions, Route Handlers, or server-only helpers). Do not query the DB directly from client components.
5. API ERROR HANDLING: Every new API route must have try/catch and log errors.

# Implementation Workflow
When I ask you to "Add a new feature":
1. Inspect the existing DB schema in `/supabase/schema.sql` (and relevant migrations) and propose the minimal migration.
2. Implement the server logic first (routes/Server Actions + types).
3. Then implement UI using existing `@/components/ui` primitives.